.Dd March 30, 2026
.Dt NEEDSUPDATE 1
.Os Kayoko
.Sh NAME
.Nm needsupdate
.Nd determine if a target file is out of date
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm needsupdate
.Ar source
.Ar target
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm needsupdate
utility compares the modification times of a
.Ar source
file and a
.Ar target
file to determine if the target needs to be rebuilt or updated.
.Pp
If
.Ar source
is newer than
.Ar target ,
or if
.Ar target
does not exist, the utility considers an update necessary.
.Pp
This is designed for use in shell scripts and build systems (like
.Xr build.lua 8 )
to avoid redundant compilation or processing steps.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The
.Nm needsupdate
utility exits with one of the following values:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It 0
The
.Ar target
is up to date (equal to or newer than
.Ar source ) .
.It 1
The
.Ar target
needs an update (older than
.Ar source
or missing).
.It 2
An error occurred, such as the
.Ar source
file not being found or insufficient permissions.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Check if a C source file has changed since the last build:
.Pp
.Dl $ needsupdate main.c main.o && cc -c main.c -o main.o
.Pp
Usage within a script to gate a slow process:
.Pp
.Dl if needsupdate data.raw data.cache; then
.Dl 	generate_cache data.raw > data.cache
.Dl fi
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr stat 2 ,
.Xr build.lua 8
